We also don't know what other health and care needs are being missed due to #COVID19. Some of this could be behind the non-COVID excess deaths we are seeing in care homes. We've also got no line of sight on the impact of those receiving social care in the community.

What was happening in care homes was hidden in the early days of the pandemic. We've not seen the same investment in using data to tackle #COVID19 in social care - this is preventing us from taking action. We've written about this here:

While the epidemic in care homes seems to be slowing, we mustn't be complacent. COVID-19 has exposed the systematic under investment in our care home and social care system. While COVID-19 is still circulating residents and staff will remain at risk.
